cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.MM

The paper deals with adaptive streaming of 360 VR videos, which involves multimedia processing (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) to represent the videos in the 3D space. It also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) to efficiently stream the videos to wireless VR headsets. Additionally, the paper mentions encoding and packaging of the videos, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia processing (cs.MM).
